17 Section 1210.508C. A. To identify students who have a reading
18 deficiency including identifying students with characteristics of
19 dyslexia, each student enrolled in kindergarten and first, second,
20 and third grade in a public school in this state shall be screened
21 at the beginning, middle, and end of each school year for reading
22 skills including, but not limited to, phonological awareness,
23 decoding, fluency, vocabulary, and comprehension. Kindergarten
24 students shall be screened at the middle and end of the school year,
